reviews.review_text: Clean, Tight, Energetic Good night for the boys. I was there, and it sounds better here than I remember it sounding in Boston. Some of the changes (HOTW, Etc.) are a little loose, but overall a great show. All voices are mixed well and sounding great, Phil is on a mission, and Billy seems to be having alot of fun. Jerry is his usual '76 searing self. Solid 4 Stars.

Serious snorting can be heard During the tuning before Playing. I like how this is tracked, but the Charlie version sounds better.
http://www.archive.org/details/gd76-06-10.sbd.miller.14264.sbeok.shnf
Kieth sounds great... Also love the Space after the playin near the end of the show!! Nice performance, new to me... as I hadn't really heard of listened to it... funny how some get past you!
